{
  "doc_id": "60400",
  "text": "The work in [CITATION_1] first subjects multiple RGB-D images to registration via 3D alignment from 3D feature point correspondences and then employs guided image filtering [CITATION_2] and a tailored SRCNN in order to obtain HR depth images. The method is illustrated in Fig. 21 . The reported results demonstrate the utility of the method when applied to ICL-NUIM [CITATION_3] , MPI-Sintel [CITATION_4] datasets, but adds little to the results of only guided image filtering [CITATION_5] in the face of additional cost involved in the form of SRCNN.",
